<topic id="canonicalizing-files">
  <title>Canonicalizing Files</title>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <indexterm>Digital Signature<indexterm>Canonicalize files</indexterm></indexterm>
        <indexterm>Canonicalize files tool</indexterm></keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <body>
    <p id="p_dn1_cgk_54b">You can select the <xref keyref="glossentry_canonicalize"
        ><term>canonicalization</term></xref> algorithm to be used for a document from the dialog
      box that is displayed by using the <uicontrol>Canonicalize</uicontrol> action that is
      available from the <uicontrol>Source</uicontrol> submenu when invoking the contextual menu in
        <uicontrol>Text</uicontrol> mode<ph product="author developer editor"> or from the
          <uicontrol>Tools</uicontrol> menu</ph><ph product="developerEclipse editorEclipse"> or
        from the <uicontrol>XML Tools</uicontrol> menu</ph>.</p>
    <p id="p_en1_cgk_54b">
      <fig product="editor author developer" id="fig_fn1_cgk_54b">
        <title>Canonicalization Settings Dialog Box</title>
        <image href="../img/sa_canonicalize_dialog.png"/>
      </fig>
    </p>
    <p id="p_gn1_cgk_54b">
      <fig product="developerEclipse editorEclipse" id="fig_hn1_cgk_54b">
        <title>Canonicalization Settings Dialog Box</title>
        <image href="../img/ec_canonicalize_dialog.png"/>
      </fig>
    </p>
    <p id="p_in1_cgk_54b">The <uicontrol>Canonicalize</uicontrol> dialog box allows you to set the following
      options:</p>
    <ul id="ul_jn1_cgk_54b">
      <li product="author developer editor developerEclipse editorEclipse" id="li_kn1_cgk_54b"><uicontrol>Input
          URL</uicontrol> - Available if the <uicontrol>Canonicalize</uicontrol> action was selected
        from the <uicontrol product="author developer editor">Tools</uicontrol><uicontrol
          product="developerEclipse editorEclipse">XML Tools</uicontrol> menu. It allows you to
        specify the location of the input file.</li>
      <li id="li_ln1_cgk_54b"><uicontrol>Exclusive</uicontrol> - If selected, the exclusive (uncommented) <xref
          keyref="glossentry_canonicalize"><term>canonicalization</term></xref> method is used.<note
          conkeyref="reusables-user-guide/exclusive-note" id="note_mn1_cgk_54b"/></li>
      <li id="li_nn1_cgk_54b"><uicontrol>Exclusive with comments</uicontrol> - If selected, the exclusive with comments
          <xref keyref="glossentry_canonicalize"><term>canonicalization</term></xref> method is
        used.</li>
      <li id="li_on1_cgk_54b"><uicontrol>Inclusive</uicontrol> - If selected, the inclusive (uncommented) <xref
          keyref="glossentry_canonicalize"><term>canonicalization</term></xref> method is used.<note
          conkeyref="reusables-user-guide/inclusive-note" id="note_pn1_cgk_54b"/></li>
      <li id="li_qn1_cgk_54b"><uicontrol>Inclusive with comments</uicontrol> - If selected, the inclusive with comments
          <xref keyref="glossentry_canonicalize"><term>canonicalization</term></xref> method is
        used.</li>
      <li id="li_rn1_cgk_54b"><uicontrol>XPath</uicontrol> - The XPath expression provides the fragments of the XML
        document to be signed.</li>
      <li product="author developer editor developerEclipse editorEclipse" id="li_sn1_cgk_54b"
          ><uicontrol>Output</uicontrol> - Available if the <uicontrol>Canonicalize</uicontrol>
        action was selected from the <uicontrol product="author developer editor"
          >Tools</uicontrol><uicontrol product="developerEclipse editorEclipse">XML
          Tools</uicontrol> menu. It allows you to specify the output file path where the signed XML
        document will be saved.</li>
      <li product="author developer editor developerEclipse editorEclipse" id="li_tn1_cgk_54b"><uicontrol>Open in
          editor</uicontrol> - If selected, the output file will be opened in the editor.</li>
    </ul>
  </body>
